                <note rend="inline" type="source">462.00 R 29/126: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wallace</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-03-26T16:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1920—4 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>617. For Rathbone from Department and Davis. R–295.</p>
                <p>Your R–446, March 22, noon. It is believed that you should maintain your former
                    position that the conference of Ambassadors <pb facs="0470" n="380"
                        xml:id="pg_380"/> cannot properly demand a report from the Reparation
                    Commission for the reasons stated in your third paragraph. However, reserving
                    all rights of the Reparation Commission we see no objection, if you approve, to
                    transmitting the information asked for as a matter of courtesy.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Colby</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
